### CSS Keyframes

**@keyframes** defines the intermediate steps of an animation.

---

### Syntax

```css
@keyframes animationName {
  from { /* Start state */ }
  to   { /* End state */ }
}

/* Or with percentage stops */
@keyframes animationName {
  0%   { /* Start */ }
  50%  { /* Middle */ }
  100% { /* End */ }
}
```

---

### From/To Syntax

Simple two-step animation:

```css
@keyframes fadeIn {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(20px);
  }
  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}
```

---

### Percentage Syntax

Multi-step animation:

```css
@keyframes pulse {
  0% {
    transform: scale(1);
    opacity: 1;
  }
  50% {
    transform: scale(1.1);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  100% {
    transform: scale(1);
    opacity: 1;
  }
}
```

---

### Common Keyframe Animations

```css
/* Slide in from left */
@keyframes slideInLeft {
  from { transform: translateX(-100%); opacity: 0; }
  to { transform: translateX(0); opacity: 1; }
}

/* Spin */
@keyframes spin {
  from { transform: rotate(0deg); }
  to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}

/* Shake */
@keyframes shake {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateX(0); }
  10%, 30%, 50%, 70%, 90% { transform: translateX(-5px); }
  20%, 40%, 60%, 80% { transform: translateX(5px); }
}

/* Color change */
@keyframes colorCycle {
  0% { background: red; }
  33% { background: blue; }
  66% { background: green; }
  100% { background: red; }
}
```

---

### Using Keyframes

```css
.element {
  animation: slideInLeft 0.5s ease forwards;
}

.loader {
  animation: spin 1s linear infinite;
}

.error {
  animation: shake 0.5s ease;
}
```

---

### Multiple Animations

```css
@keyframes slideIn {
  from { transform: translateX(-100%); }
  to { transform: translateX(0); }
}

@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; }
}

.element {
  animation: slideIn 0.5s ease, fadeIn 0.3s ease;
}
```

> **Key Point:** Animation names are case-sensitive. Use descriptive names like `fadeIn`, `slideUp`, `spin`.
